text.section:
The Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City or the governing body of a county or municipal corporation shall provide, by law, for:
the amount of the property tax credit authorized under this section for each taxable year after the purchase of the residential real property;
the designation of certain geographic areas as neighborhood conservation areas for purposes of the tax credit authorized under this section;
any additional limitations on eligibility for the credit under this section; and
any other provision necessary to implement the credit under this section.

On or before January 1, of the calendar year following the year in which the neighborhood conservation tax credit is initiated, and each January 1 thereafter, a county or municipal corporation that grants a tax credit under this section shall submit a report, in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, to the Senate Budget and Taxation Committee and the House Ways and Means Committee that describes:
the tax credit program;
the designated neighborhood conservation areas;
the number of residential properties within neighborhood conservation areas that qualify for the tax credit under this section; and
the economic impact of the tax credits granted under this section on the neighborhood conservation areas.
